############################
### Monte Carlo Analysis ###
############################
A set of C++ files which form a small library to perform analyses on different types of files produced
by Monte Carlo generators. The file types are all based on a common <particle> class and inherit from it.

Based on the <particle> class there will be an <event> class containing a list of particles. Event 
samples can be constructed by making a vector of <event> objects. 

On these event samples one can perform basic analyses like cut and count. For this we produced the <cut>
class in which one can implement an analysis.


####################
### Dependencies ###
####################
Folder /deps ignored by git and used to put in external libraries. This folder should contain the following
libraries:
 * gzstream: library from http://www.cs.unc.edu/Research/compgeom/gzstream/ and make it.

Other dependencies are:
 * C++ standard library: included in any recent compiler
 * boost: take the latest release from http://www.boost.org/users/download/
 * python: should be on any system, version 2.7 needed
 * root: follow instructions from http://root.cern.ch/drupal/content/installing-root-source
 * pythia: latest release from http://home.thep.lu.se/~torbjorn/Pythia.html
 * fastjet: latest release from http://fastjet.fr/all-releases.html and make it
 * hepmc: take from http://lcgapp.cern.ch/project/simu/HepMC/ and include in pythia


######################
### Particle Class ###
######################
The <particle> class serves as a base class for different object formats like .lhco and .lhe. These formats
are then derived classes from the <particle> class called <lhco> and <lhe>.


